# Git mailmap for author normalization
# Format: Preferred Name <preferred@email> Commit Name <commit@email>
#
# This file ensures consistent author attribution across commits, especially when:
# - Contributors use different email addresses (work/personal)
# - Contributors change their name or email
# - Multiple accounts are used
#
# See: https://git-scm.com/docs/gitmailmap

# Example entries (replace with actual contributors):
# John Doe <john@example.com> john <john@old-email.com>
# Jane Smith <jane@example.com> <jane-old@example.com>
